ring modes of problematization as modes of inhabitation, the volume maps its current conceptual-political uses as well as onto-epistemological challenges. Thus, »problematization« is positioned as a critical concept.  afunded by VolkswagenStiftung  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aKnowledge, Theory ofvCongresses. 0aPhilosophy. 0aSciencexPhilosophyvCongresses. 4aFrench History of Philosophy. 4aHistory of Philosophy. 4aHistory of Science. 4aPhilosophy of Science. 4aPhilosophy. 4aProblematic. 4aScience. 4aSustainability. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh  aFrench History of Philosophy.  aHistory of Philosophy.  aHistory of Science.  aPhilosophy of Science.  aPhilosophy.  aProblematic.  aScience.  aSustainability.1 aBrunner, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbke, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeistert, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeistert, Oliver, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLury, Celia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Esther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSavransky, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchrickel, Isabell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchrickel, Isabell, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVuillerod, Jean-Baptiste, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb2 aVolkswagenStiftungefunder.4fnd4http://id.lo